snippet.textDisplay:
The CGI for these movies reminded me of Momma, and I couldn’t take the “scares” seriously. Maybe practical effects would’ve worked better. I couldn’t help but giggle when the woman in the painting in Part I comes to life, and I outright laughed at the scene with adult Bev and the old woman in Part II.

Also, the tone was off. I’m not sure if it was actually trying to be a “horror movie” or a haunted house ride with dark humor. Lots of interesting choices were made for a movie this expensive with such a A list cast.

I did enjoy seeing Pennywise “drop the bass” on Bill Hader’s character though. That was great.
snippet.textOriginal:

Also, the tone was off. I’m not sure if it was actually trying to be a “horror movie” or a haunted house ride with dark humor. Lots of interesting choices were made for a movie this expensive with such a A list cast.
